args: Form up!\nAt this rate we'll be wiped out!
Too late for that! You guys ready?
...And that's that. Pack up, gang—we're\nmovin' on.
I won't let you get away, Cruor Hounds...
Hey, {player_name}! You seen\nol' Big and Beefy around?
You mean Ranzal? Not since this morning.\nIs everything all right?
He's still not back from patrol. I'm thinking\nsomethin' might'a happened.
Hmm. Okay, let's go take a look at\nhis patrol route.
Still kickin' after that lickin', huh?\nNot bad.
Heh. Thanks, but I'm not really lookin'\nfor praise from the fella what jumped\nme outta nowhere.
Ha ha! Fair enough. Guess we better finish\nyou off then.
Regal-lookin' blonde... I reckon that's\nour prey.
Pretty nice of ya to come face us yourself.
Watch yourself, boss. This guy's got the\nbite to match his bark.
They call him the Mad Dog.
In the flesh. Name's Durant—the Mad Dog\nof Valkaheim.
I lead a resistance group based outta\nValkaheim itself. We call ourselves the\nCruor Hounds.
If you're from Valkaheim, what are you\ndoing here?
I'm here to recruit you, of course.
Oh, sure. You want his castle, too?\nFree with every purchase!
Wise guy, huh?\nHey boys—take care'a this runt.
If you're gonna sass me, we're gonna\nbash you!
They really can't take a joke!\nThis could be bad.
This is no place for us to be fighting!
There he is! The Mad Dog!
It seems we were right to make chase.\nWait a second... Is that the traitorous\nprince?!
Imperials?! You're just a bundle'a bad\nnews, huh?
Tch. And we were just gettin' to the good\nstuff. Sort them out, gang!
We'll have both of your lives here!\nHaaaah!
You stay put, blondie. These guys are\nOUR prey!
Show 'em your fangs, Hounds!\nAnd no dyin'!
Yeah. It's not so much their individual\nstrength, but how effectively they\nwork together.

What'd ya expect from a bunch what set
up shop in Valkaheim? The strong eat
the weak in that city; even the Empire's
threatened by 'em.
Oi! You think you can nip at the Mad Dog\nwithout getting bitten yourself?!
Boss, why the heck did ya take that hit\nfor me?!
You idiot, I wasn't takin' a hit for you.\nYou were bein' slow, so I knocked ya out\nof my way.
But whatever. We live to fight another day.\nNow we just gotta deal with YOU runts.
C'mon, boss, you can't go fightin' with\nthat wound...
Yeah, about that—what're we gonna do?\nClosest town's a way's off, but the boss\nmight not have that long...
Guess we've only got one choice then.
Please, {player_name}—help our\nboss out! I'm beggin' ya!
I know how this makes us look, but...\nPlease.
If you save our boss, my life is yours!
The hell?! Who said you could go tradin'\nyour life away?! I'll show ya who's—urk!
Boss, ya gotta lie still for now.
We can't leave him like this.
As if he'd say anything else. All right,\nbozos, pick up yer boss and follow me.
You two are gonna pay for this...
As long as it means you get to live,\nwe'll take whatever you can throw.
Heh. Idiot. I'll make you regret...that...\nNn...
Is it really such a good idea though,\nbringin' the Mad Dog into the Halidom?\nNot sure he's really, er...house-trained.
We can't send him away while he's\ninjured—especially when he saved\nus from those imperials.
*sigh* Yeah, yeah. Fine. I'm not gonna let\nhim off for sluggin' me though.
But I guess as long as he's here, I can get\nhim back whenever I want. Heh!
The Mad Dog of Valkaheim... Who knows\nwhere things are headed next.
